ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Treatment type
Notes: 1 = CBT; 2 = PT; 3 = PT and CBT

ElementDescription: Weeks from Time 0/baseline to assessment
Session Type
Notes: 1 = Office; 2 = Phone

ElementDescription: The therapists explanation of what depression is made sense to me
Notes: 1 = Strongly disagree 2 = disagree 3 = Somewhat agree 4 = agree 5 = Strongly agree

ElementDescription: The therapists explanation of what cognitive behavior therapy is made sense to me
Notes: 1 = Strongly disagree 2 = disagree 3 = Somewhat agree 4 = agree 5 = Strongly agree

ElementDescription: The therapists explanation of how cognitive behavior therapy will help made sense to me
Notes: 1 = Strongly disagree 2 = disagree 3 = Somewhat agree 4 = agree 5 = Strongly agree

ElementDescription: I expect to get control over depression through this program
Notes: 1 = Strongly disagree 2 = disagree 3 = Somewhat agree 4 = agree 5 = Strongly agree

ElementDescription: I expect to get better or become less depressed through this program
Notes: 1 = Strongly disagree 2 = disagree 3 = Somewhat agree 4 = agree 5 = Strongly agree

ElementDescription: I expect my life to get better in some ways through this program
Notes: 1 = Strongly disagree 2 = disagree 3 = Somewhat agree 4 = agree 5 = Strongly agree

ElementDescription: Study stage
Notes: 0 = Pre-Randomization (TADS) 1 = Stage 1 (TADS) 2 = Stage 2 (TADS) 3 = Stage 3 (TADS) 4 = Stage 4 (TADS) 5 = Stage 5 (SOFTAD); 51=Treatmentas Usual; 52=Screening Alone; 53=Intervention; 67=Unknown; -888=Not Applicable; -999=Missing;

ElementDescription: Visit name
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2

ElementDescription: Number of days from study baseline to date of visit

Parent/Child: 1. How much do you expect that doing cognitive-behavioral therapy will affect your anxiety problems?  If treated with cognitive-behavior therapy only, I expect my anxiety problems will be...
Notes: 1 = Very Much Improved; 2 = Much Improved; 3 = Minimally Improved; 4 = No Change; 5 = Minimally Worse; 6 = Much Worse; 7 = Very Much Worse

ElementDescription: Parent/Child : 2. How much do you expect that medication will affect your anxiety problems?  If treated with medication only, I expect my anxiety problems will be...
Notes: 1 = Very Much Improved; 2 = Much Improved; 3 = Minimally Improved; 4 = No Change; 5 = Minimally Worse; 6 = Much Worse; 7 = Very Much Worse

ElementDescription: Parent/Child : 3. How much do you expect that doing cognitive-behavioral therapy plus taking medication will affect your anxiety problems? If treated with a combination of cognitive-behavior therapy plus medication, I expect my anxiety problems will be...
Notes: 1 = Very Much Improved; 2 = Much Improved; 3 = Minimally Improved; 4 = No Change; 5 = Minimally Worse; 6 = Much Worse; 7 = Very Much Worse

ElementDescription: Parent/Child : Pre-Treatment Expectancy of Treatment Assigned
Notes: 1 = Very Much Improved; 2 = Much Improved; 3 = Minimally Improved; 4 = No Change; 5 = Minimally Worse; 6 = Much Worse; 7 = Very Much Worse

ElementDescription: Parent : Pre-Treatment Expectancies Informant Informant(s)
Notes: 2 = mother; 3 = father; 5 = both parents; 7 = aunt/uncle; 8 = grandparent; 9 = other

ElementDescription: Parent : Pre-Treatment Expectancies Informant Other Informant(s)
Parent : Pre-Treatment Expectancies Informant Derived
Notes: 2 = mother; 3 = father; 5 = both parents; 7 = aunt/uncle; 8 = grandparent; 9 = other

ElementDescription: Respondent
Notes: NA=Not Applicable

ElementDescription: Respondent: Other (specify)
The relationship of the respondent to subject
Treatment Condition
Notes: 1 = Sertraline/Cognitive Behavioral Therapy; 2 = Sertraline only; 3 = Cognitive Behavioral Therapy only; 4 = Placebo; 9 = Completely uncertain (GUESE only)

ElementDescription: Any Co-morbidity (0,1,2+)
Notes: 0 = no co-morbidity; 1 = one co-morbidity; 2 = two or more co-morbidities

Notes: 0 = no; 1 = yes

ElementDescription: Any Externalizing Diagnoses
Notes: 0 = no; 1 = yes
